Blood refers to the presence of a small amount of blood in a petтАЩs urine and is determined by measuring the amount of hemoglobin and myoglobin in urine. Mostly, if there is an abnormality in the urinary system (e.g. kidney, urethra, bladder, urethra, etc.), it will be shown as positive. Healthy pets may also get a positive test results temporarily.

Bilirubin is a metabolite of hemoglobin, a component of red blood cells. A negative reaction should be shown in the petтАЩs urine. For dogs (especially males), mild positive reactions may be common, even under normal conditions. However, for cats, you need to be careful even you get mild positive results.

Urovillinogens are formed in the process of dissolving hemoglobin, and intestinal bacteria convert bilirubin into ureobilinogens. A small amount may be detected in healthy pets, but if a large amount is detected, it may be possible to suspect haemolytic or malignant anemia.

Keatonin is an metabolite of fatty acids produced by the decomposition of the lipid,and is produced by increased in vivo fat decomposition if insulin or carbohydrate intake is insufficient. Only a small amount should be detected from healthy pets.
A small amount of protein can be detected (proteinurized) in the urine of healthy pets, but a large amount of protein can be found in both kidney and non-renatal diseases.
Nitrates absorbed through food are decomposed into nitrates by infected bacteria and are detected in the urine of pets. Small amounts can also be detected in healthy pets.

Glucose is an important source of energy and all must be absorbed by body in the case of healthy pets. However, very thiny amounts can be detected if your pets over-consume sugary food before the test of if they are under a lot of stress.

pH indicates the degree of acidity and alkaline in urine and is determined by the kidneyтАЩs ability which control the concentration of hydrogen ions and bicarbonates in the blood. If your pets eat a lot of high-protein meat, it becomes acidic; if you eat a lot of vegetables, it becomes alkaline.

Urine Specific Gravity indicates urine concentration based on water density and is a useful indicator of dilution and enrichment of the kidneys. Urine is dark in the case of high specific gravity and light in the case of low specific gravity.

White blood cells, one of the cells that make up the blood, is responsible for the immunity of pets through phagocytosis. In the case of bacterial infection in the urinary system, the white blood cells in the body increase and can also be detected in urine.

Blood refers to the presence of a small amount of blood in a petтАЩs urine and is determined by measuring the amount of hemoglobin and myoglobin in urine. Mostly, if there is an abnormality in the urinary system (e.g. kidney, urethra, bladder, urethra, etc.), it will be shown as positive. Healthy pets may also get a positive test results temporarily.

Bilirubin is a metabolite of hemoglobin, a component of red blood cells. A negative reaction should be shown in the petтАЩs urine. For dogs (especially males), mild positive reactions may be common, even under normal conditions. However, for cats, you need to be careful even you get mild positive results.

Urovillinogens are formed in the process of dissolving hemoglobin, and intestinal bacteria convert bilirubin into ureobilinogens. A small amount may be detected in healthy pets, but if a large amount is detected, it may be possible to suspect haemolytic or malignant anemia.

Keatonin is an metabolite of fatty acids produced by the decomposition of the lipid,and is produced by increased in vivo fat decomposition if insulin or carbohydrate intake is insufficient. Only a small amount should be detected from healthy pets.
A small amount of protein can be detected (proteinurized) in the urine of healthy pets, but a large amount of protein can be found in both kidney and non-renatal diseases.
Nitrates absorbed through food are decomposed into nitrates by infected bacteria and are detected in the urine of pets. Small amounts can also be detected in healthy pets.

Glucose is an important source of energy and all must be absorbed by body in the case of healthy pets. However, very thiny amounts can be detected if your pets over-consume sugary food before the test of if they are under a lot of stress.

pH indicates the degree of acidity and alkaline in urine and is determined by the kidneyтАЩs ability which control the concentration of hydrogen ions and bicarbonates in the blood. If your pets eat a lot of high-protein meat, it becomes acidic; if you eat a lot of vegetables, it becomes alkaline.

Urine Specific Gravity indicates urine concentration based on water density and is a useful indicator of dilution and enrichment of the kidneys. Urine is dark in the case of high specific gravity and light in the case of low specific gravity.

White blood cells, one of the cells that make up the blood, is responsible for the immunity of pets through phagocytosis. In the case of bacterial infection in the urinary system, the white blood cells in the body increase and can also be detected in urine.

Q. After put the urine on the test strip, when do i have to test(photo shot)?

A. Inspection through the test strip ensures approximately 99% reliability, but may also be affected by the what they ate right before the test and by photographic environment (light interference). Q. How often should I checkup?
A. If your pets do not have a "Doubt" or "Danger" diease result, we recommend a monthly test

A. This product provides useful clinical information by metabolism, new function, liver function, acid salt equilibrium, and urinary tract infection through urine test.
